In article <168C413C13.UC445585@mizzou1.missouri.edu> UC445585@mizzou1.missouri.edu (John M. Kelsey) writes:
>   Why did PGP change from bassomatic to IDEA?  Where can I find references
>to IDEA?  (It's Swiss?)
 
X. Lai and J. Massey, "A Proposal for a New Block Encryption Standard,"
Advances in Cryptology: Proceedings of Eurocrypt 90, Springer-Verlag, 1991,
pp. 389-404.

X. Lai, J. Massey, and S. Murphy, "Markov Ciphers and Differential 
Cryptanalysis," Advances in Cryptology: Proceedings of Eurocrypt 91, Springer-
Verlag, 1991, pp. 17-38.

X. Lai and J. Massey, "Hash Functions Based on Block Ciphers," Advances in
Cryptology: Proceedings of Eurocrypt 92, Springer-Verlag, to appear.

X. Lai, "On the Design and Security of Block Ciphers," ETH Series in
Information Processing, Volume 1, Hartung-Gorre Verlag, Konstanz, 1992.

The fifth reference is best, but very hard to get.  The third reference is
also good, albeit much shorter.  Source code for IDEA is in PGP.

Bruce
